unsearchable adjective
(NOT KNOWABLE)
formal old-fashioned mysterious and impossible to understand: He gazed into the unsearchable abyss of her dark eyes. The apostle spoke of the gospel as containing something that was unsearchable.
More examplesFewer examplesThe Scripture says that God's ways are unsearchable.He will tell you great and unsearchable things you do not know.He stopped being a teacher to preach the unsearchable riches of Christ.
